The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Jones hopes to tour India

London: England pacer Simon Jones is confident of featuring in the squad during Englands tour of India in February after undergoing surgery on his right ankle. 

Jones, 26, missed the final Ashes Test against Australia with a bone spur injury in September and has pulled out of next months Pakistan tour following a recent operation. 

The operation went really well and I am feeling really good and really positive, said Jones on Wednesday. 

Ill be running again in six weeks and bowling again in seven or eight, so Im really looking forward to it. 

The India tour is a massive possibility ?? its what I am aiming for. Im not doing this rehab for no reason. 

Jones is no stranger to layoffs having been sidelined for 16 months after a serious knee injury in Australia in 2002. 

